You can set static IP address in your rooter interface.
Info may be on the back of your rooter if not try below:
  Most have this basic feature standard rooters IP is something like 192.168.0.1 or 192.168.1.1
  If not start a DOS command prompt (cmd) and type ipconfig /all and make a note of the DHCP server address.
  Enter that ip into the address bar of your web browser and log in.
Look for LAN setting
Look for DHCP settings and folow onscreen prompts.
